    "title": "Pascal's Triangle II",
    "workload": "each rep computes the rowIndex-th Pascal row for a data-dependent rowIndex (30+acc%20, so 30..49, seeded by the running hash so get_row() can't be hoisted), building one Vec[i64] of length rowIndex+1 and updating it IN PLACE right-to-left (row[k]=row[k]+row[k-1]), folding every entry; K=440000 reps \u2014 the in-place index-assignment regime (a single small Vec per rep, dominated by the O(k^2) in-place updates)",
